ratings.rComments: Very nice guy, pretty quirky, and a great lecturer. He makes the material very interesting and easy to understand. Tests are a little difficult (you need to read the book), but nothing too bad. He curves the tests and also the class at the end (very generously). Overall, great teacher, great class. Wish he taught more courses!
Easy A but the readings do take long. Lectures are long and boring.  No homeworkquizzes and only 4 tests and subject pool.  It took me two days to prepare for the tests.

Easy class but poorly organized with little hope of actually learning material. Without a curve, nobody would pass the class. Exam questions are on specific studies he mentions briefly in class, and you cannot look up the study on your own since he doesn't cite them. Do not take this class if you are genuinely interested in the topic.

You have to attend every lecture and take good notes, but you can get away with cramming the chapters the night before and get an A.  Very funny and likeable professor. Made the class go faster with his anecdotes.

He's a pretty goofy guy but he knows psychology in and out. He has interesting stories and gives good examples. He teaches section X, which is different from any of the other sections. There is no homework just 4 exams and a subject pool. His exams are pretty hard, but he uses a generous curve. Just go to class, take notes, read the book, and study
A is manageable if you read the book and attend lectures. Exams are tricky, but the curve is forgiving. Overall pretty fun class.

I don't know how this class got a reputation of being easy, it is anything but easy. The only "easy" part of this class is that there is no homework except reading. Curve isn't that crazy as people made it seem. Take the regular section.

Srull is a pretty good professor. Class is not mandatory and can be boring but it is helpful for the exams.  He explains things very clearly and simply.  Exams are tough but if you read the book and go to class it is not bad.  Very generous curve.

He's a good professor. Going to class and taking notes is a must as some of the stuff he says literally shows up word for word on the exams. Sometimes he will talk about one bullet point for almost 30 minutes but once you get past his style of lecturing, it's a good class. Curve is generous just make sure you read all the sections from the book
Uses overhead projectors with minimum words and goes off on pointless tangents. There are about 10 chapters to read in the textbook for the exam, and his exams are very specific and very hard.

This class had only three exams, and there were no essays, no participation, and no textbook. That being said, it is very important to go to lecture, even if it is not mandatory. The lectures were easy to follow, albeit boring at times, and the exams were not bad either. I am not a psyc major but I could take this class without any problems.

Pure audible lecture. Non-relevant tangents. Doesn't teach the non course related textbook (right-wing biased with cherry-picked studies). Curved exams yes, but with the grounds of arbitrary questions.
Don't even bother going to his class! EVERYTHING is from the book, and the exams are too hard for this level.

TOO EASY. Go to lecture, listen, and read what he assigns. Takes like 3 days at a slow pace to read it all. His exams are tricky but not terrible and don't worry, his curve is pretty much ridiculous (in a good way). Easiest class I had this semester. NO homeowork, no stress. Just 4 exams and 6 subject pool experiments. Easy A

Just a classic lecture with over three hundred people. Typical aloof professor, although he spoke plainly and was not condescending for the most part. Not having a discussion section made the class pretty impersonal and a little more difficult than it would have normally been. Enjoyed multiple choice tests and there was a curve.
Amazing lecturer. Very interested in the topic and knowledgeable. Friendly, helpful, enthusiastic.
After every class I feel as though I had just witnessed a ground-breaking speech. Srull presents information in a crystal clear manner. He is very easy to follow.
Very good lecturer - Never had trouble understanding/following what he was saying. Though not mandatory, lectures are a must. Must read the textbook as well. Very interesting class.

The class is easy enough if you STUDY for the exam, READ the textbook, and ATTEND & take notes at all lectures. Lectures can be dull though, as he tends to be THOROUGH w/materials. but he is very helpful if you have any questions before and during exams. The curve for the class is generous.

He might be sort of odd and quirky in personality but in my opinion he's an interesting lecturer. Content of the course was intriguing. He can be pretty funny when he wants to. You HAVE to go to class and MUST do the reading in order to even have a chance on the exams. exams are decently curved, he's pretty generous.

If you want an A, memorize all the vocab, important names, experiments, and take detailed notes in lecture. Type your lecture notes because he can go deep into detail. Consider buying the study guide, it helped me a lot. Some practice questions in there end up on the exam. You can get an A as long as you are willing to work for it. Decent lecturer.

The hardest part of this class was the sheer amount of information stuffed into 4 exams with 55 questions. The readings and the lectures were totally unrelated but both were on the exam. Curve was EXTREMELY generous however.
Very nice and helpful

one of the worst professors i've ever had. he mumbles a lot, repeats the same sentence 10 times at a rate of 0.2 mph, his lectures aren't clear. you have to read the textbook because its on the exam but he doesn't go over anything that's in the book. exams are harder than you'd expect

His is fun and states everything clearly in the lecture. You should write some notes in lecture and also read some book, but materials are not hard. So as long as you attend the lecture and read book, you will get an A.

By Jove, I could not figure out why his teeth are disgusting. They were so distracting even when I sat in the back. Anyway, READ the book AND go to class. Failed the first test because I did neither, and ended up with a B. I redeemed myself with 3 more tests and a generous curve. Do the subject pool, it's required. That's how idiots get C's.

This class should be easy, 4 NONCONSECUTIVE exams and 6 subject pool participations, however if you never have taken a psych class (like me) DO NOT take this class with him. I feel like this class is easier for ppl who have prior knowledge. His examples go on for 20 minutes and lectures seem to take forever. He does curve the grades, which is aplus
Great teacher. The material is interesting and the tests are not hard as long as you attend/pay attention in lecture AND read the assigned chapters.

Read the textbook, go to class and take a lot of notes. With these, you'll do great one the exam. For the first exam, 43/50 = A. Material is interesting though, so its not too hard to concentrate. If that doesn't work for you, bring a recorder.

I liked Srull. I think he does tend to lose track of himself every so often, but that's part of the fun. Read the book, no really, do it, and take notes in class no matter how he rambles, and you'll be good to go. Three exams make up your grade, but they are curved significantly. Social Cognition was really interesting.

He does ramble in the class, some people get bored, but exams are fine if you study both lecture notes and textbooks. My highest exam score: 47/50. Make sure you read textbooks thoroughly. If you miss class then get notes from classmates, since he doesn't post it online. Be aware that his letter grade don't include +/- so it's either A or B.

avoid this class i hated srull. awful professor should not be here. sucks. if you are a freshman don't take this class until your sophomore year or atleast until your g.p.a. is high enough to handle the toll this class will take on it. i cannot tell you to avoid this class enough. BOOOOO!!!

A few ?s... 1. Why is this awful professor rated so high on this website 2. Why is professor at U of I. The avg of each of the tests is a D and then gets curved, why is that positive? Lecture is awful and hard to follow. I would say read the book but that might not help. Take psych at a community college or something, not with this guy!

If you are a good test taker or have previously taken AP Psych definitely take PSYC 100 Section X with Srull! Just show up to class, take notes, manage your time well so you can finish the module readings and you will get an A. The psych studies are interesting and some of them pay you for participating. This is a very straight forward class.

Although attendence is not mandatory, getting an A in this class is highly dependent on your regular attendance. Srull is an entertaining professor and keeps students' attention fairly well. Make sure you read the book, because he will pull about 25-30% of the exam questions from it.

What a dreadful professor. Rambles on with unrelated anecdotes and focuses on topics really unrelated to social cognition. We spent the last few weeks on evolutionary psychology for gods sakes. I'm not sure what we learned in this class that's related to social cognition at all. Pretty easy class though if you can stand to go to class.

The only grades come from exams which are *mostly* lecture based, so go to lectures. He explains things very thoroughly, which can be helpful, but also boring at times. The exams are not too hard, and are curved. My raw score was 78% which ended up being a solid A.

Awesome teacher.Class is interesting/funny and hes reasonable.changed a test two days before we were supposed to have it because someone raised their hand and asked him to bc of the heavy reading load,so he held a class vote right there. Going to class is pretty crucial, not mandatory.Worst part of the class is the book, which you do need to read.

i thought X would be a breeze, and granted it prolly would have been if id tried harder. class was boring to me because it took him 10 minutes to get through one example, so i got frustrated listening to him. but if you pay attention, read the book, you'll do fine.

only 4 difficult test. Half the material comes from the book, half from lecture, and he doesn't talk about whats in the book at all. Very difficult class, stressful, do not take sectin X. He doesn't have office hours. Sometimes hes interesting and funny, but i would rather it not be funny and get a good grade...

I'm torn. The pros to the class are that there are just 4 tests and that there are no other academic commitments for the class with the exception of the subject pools. The cons are that the subject matter is boring and just skims the surface. He seems nice enough, although I never actually got to know him.

Okay. I'm confused. Everyone is saying this class was hard? What??? This was the easiest class I've taken BY FAR at UIUC. All you have to do is go to lecture (his tests use examples STRAIGHT from it), read the book, and memorize the definitions. Ignore the people saying it was hard- they have to be Communication majors or something... so easy...

I had him for Psych100X freshman year and he was AWFUL. but then I took Psych353, social cognition, with him and he was AMAZING. So much better to upperclassmen then he was to the freshmen. Tests were easy if you went and took notes and paid attention. Couple questions from the book on each test. Highly recommend this class!
his test have almost nothing to do with his lectures or the books and your grade only consists of 4 tests. Do not take this class.
Overall he's a bad professor.  This is supposed to be an intro course, and he doesn't offer office hours, and tests extremely difficult material from the book.  Only good part of is the curve.

whoever writes on here that the class is easy they are lying, it consists of 4 ridiculously hard tests, i read all the chapters and still did bad on them...when he talks in lecture its boring and really hard to pay attention to,and to be honest doesnt help on the tests, i have no idea what more to do to do good on the tests take normal psych not X!

Teacher definitely likes to talk, classes is better than most, but I still fell asleep. All the points are based on 3 tests, but there is a HUGE curve, so as long as you somewhat pay attention and study, you should least get a "B". Lectures are different from the book, but your expected to know both for the test.
VERY fair with the curve. Must go to class and do the readings if you want a good grade. Very funny guy. You have to be willing to put in time for this class, but it's worth it!!

Loved this class!  The topics were interesting and he gave fun examples.  One of the few classes where I enjoyed going and didn't want to miss lecture.  He tests over the book but doesn't teach from it.  The book is kind of confusing, but overall the class is pretty easy.  Don't talk during class or leave early.
going to class and taking notes is vital, along with reading the book... the class is heavily curved, with the cutoff for an A being 199/240 this semester.. which isn't difficult to pull off

Section x is a lot easier than the other psych 100 classes. You don't learn as much, but it is worth it for the gen ed. Some reading, but not as much as the other sections. Also, he loves the sound of his voice! His examples can go on for over 20 min. Overall the class is okay, i would take it again

He really does know how to beat a dead horse, that's for sure. He'll exhaust examples to the last syllable, this guy loves the sound of his own voice. I really didn't think he was that great of a teacher, personally, but the class was okay and it wasn't that difficult if you studied and read the book. definitely don't talk in class or leave early.
What a great guy! He's really funny and knows what he's talking about. Go to class, take notes, and read the book liberally and you'll be fine. Highly recommended!

rambles on about so much stuff, pure auditory lecture. covers too much stuff, and book sections that we are expected to know have nothing to do with what is in class. take it if you like taking a lot a lot a lot of notes and trying to pay attention to a rambling professor, not knowing about what you'll be assessed with.

Loved this class! I took 100x with him freshman year and liked him so much I took this as a non-major when I saw he was teaching it. Tends to beat examples into the ground which can get kind of boring, but overall a pretty easy and interesting class. DO THE READING!!!
Don't take the regular psych 100! This one is less work and you probably will get a laugh in every lecture.

This professor issues exams which are significantly based on his lectures. Textbook material is rarely discussed but is necessary to do well on the exam, however. There were no review sheets handed out for all 3 exams (that's all the work that is required), which makes it harder to study for. No EC/quizzes to raise grade, so don't screw up there.
he was a really great professor!! you have to go to class and take notes and read the book for tests. Great guy!!!

Interesting class and very fun teacher! However, you should attend class to take notes and you have to read if you want to get an A in the class. Amusing stories in class, but it can sometimes get a little boring. And DO NOT talk during lecture!
MUST go to class to take notes...I had to get a D on the first exam to realize that. Other than that, he's rather amusing. Just for the love of god, don't talk during class or come in late.
I had fun in this class. Good professor :)

Great and rewarding class! Although I was able to ace all the exams, it was not without work. Make sure you read all the text and go to all of the studies! it is very important to read the text and go to lecture and take notes. However, if you can read all the text in a couple of days, that is all the studying you should need to do before the exam.
Take this class!!!

Love the class!  The prof is hilarious and the material is interesting...only the last two sections though.  The first third is kind of dry, as is any introductory material.  All you have to do is go to class, take notes, and read the book...you'll be guaranteed an A!

Had him in an intro to psych class maybe 10 years ago.  Full of himself and completely unsympathetic.  As a teacher for the last 7 years, I'd say the only thing I learned from him was how not to treat students.
Read the book. Go to class. He's funny.

all you have to do in order to get an A is take notes from the lecture and read. he makes his test half from lecture, half from the book. this is the first class ive actually read the book and i needed to. its not hard and as long as you were at lecture. good teacher. lectures can be a little dry though

Lectures were boring in the beginning, but got progressively more interesting.  Class is fairly easy.  Lots of reading though.  Make sure you do the practice problems at the end of each module because he takes many of his test questions straight from those.  Threw lots of random questions though which hurt my grade.
Easy if your read the book and take good notes. 4 exams and one subject pool. The curve ended up being 200/240 for an A

Read the book and take as much notes as possible in lecture. He tends to go off on stupid tangents, but also very likely to throw a curveball question on the test. Hes kind of a wierd guy but funny at times.

Lectures are funny, but the exams can be hard if you don't read the book.  Notes pretty much mean nothing, just read the book and do the chapter exams.  I missed an A by like 2 points, so make sure you get as many problems right on the exams.
There are 4 tests each worth 55 points and a subject pool worth 20. read the book, especially the end questions because they are always on the tests.  Easy A if you read . . .
Funny lectures.  If you read and study you'll be fine.  Some test questions are taken straight from the end of the modules in the book.

If you read the book, you will get A after the curve for sure. So, read it! Go to the lectures. He's not boring, he's fun to listen to even though he repeats himself 3 times on everything. Doing experiments are annoy!! But it helps your grade.

Was funny and made class interesting, but got redundant at times and his exam questions are very particular. You have to read to do well, but the book is a pretty easy read. The study questions at the end of each module are sometimes word for word on the exam so study them, and take notes in class!!

Tries hard to make lectures interesting. Quite amusing. Strict bell curve. Don't be late to class. It's impossible to get a hold of him, no email or office hours. Specific questions about the experiments in the modules are asked in tests.

Good lecturer, funny, intelligent, but completely inaccessible like most in psych department.  Recommend class, but intro class is much harder than it should be.  Many get C or below, note strict bell curve, i.e. C is average.

You have to read the many many "modules" if you want to do well in the class, b/c lecture material is hardly on the tests.  Look over the study guides and end of module questions and they will prepare you for test. he also curves final grades ve
i thought his class was extremly difficult and he hardly taught anything in class that was on the 4 tests
Read and the stuff isn't hard.  75 minutes is a lil rough, but, but the tests and curve were easy enough.
Interesting lectures, a sense of humor. However he's incredibly inaccessible, no office hours, no email, just before or after class.
interesting lectures... not too boring, a lot of reading
if you read its not too hard, class is boring tho
Funny lecturer, but material on tests is not really taught in class.
Made a real effort
No Comments
No Comments
good teacher, great lecturer, doesn't teach material for mid-term/final
wierd guy, easy enough class
good lecturer, will keep you awake in class
